        "URL": "data:text/html;charset=utf-8,%3C!doctype%20html%3E%0A%3Chtml%20lang%3D%22%22%3E%0A%3Chead%3E%0A%20%20%3Cmeta%20charset%3D%22utf-8%22%3E%0A%20%20%3Ctitle%3EHourly%20Kitten%3C%2Ftitle%3E%0A%3C%2Fhead%3E%0A%3Cbody%3E%0A%3Cbody%3E%0A%3Ch1%20align%3D%22center%22%3EHourly%20Kitten%3C%2Fh1%3E%0A%0A%3Cdiv%20align%3D%22center%22%20id%3D%22embed%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%0A%0A%3Cul%3E%0A%3Cli%3EFediverse%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fbotsin.space%2F%40hourlykitten%22%20rel%3D%22me%22%3E%40hourlykitten%40botsin.space%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3C%2Ful%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EThe%20Hourly%20Kitten%20service%20aims%20to%20provide%20you%20with%20one%20properly%20attributed%2C%0ACreative%20Commons%20licensed%2C%20and%20mind-numbingly%20adorable%20kitten%20image%2C%20once%20an%0Ahour%2C%20on%20the%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EHourly%20Kitten%20was%20originally%20created%0Aby%20Dan%20and%20Jeremy%20Bornstein%20%E2%80%94%20Dan's%20idea%2C%20Jeremy's%20code%2C%20Dan's%20kitten%0Acuration%20%E2%80%94%20over%20the%20course%20of%20a%20few%20days%20in%20May%20and%20June%20of%202014.%20It%0Astarted%20as%20a%20Twitter%20bot.%20It%20was%20ported%20to%20the%20Fediverse%20in%20November%20of%202022.%0AAs%20of%20mid-2023%2C%20the%20Twitter%20bot%20stopped%20working%20due%20to%20adverse%20actions%20by%20the%0Afolks%20that%20run%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EThe%20impetus%20for%20the%20account%20was%20that%0ADan's%20previous%20favorite%20Twitter%20source%20of%20kittens%20started%20posting%0Away%20too%20many%20commercial%20links.%20Dan%20likes%20kittens%2C%20and%20particularly%0Afound%20that%20he%20likes%20using%20pictures%20of%20kittens%20as%20a%20way%20to%20punctuate%0Ahis%20social%20feed%20(helping%20him%20not%20lose%20his%20place%20when%20trying%20to%0Aconsume%20his%20feed%20in%20toto).%20So%2C%20he%20wanted%20to%20have%20a%20better%20source%0Aof%20kittens%2C%20with%20a%20reasonably%20memorable%20(and%20stately)%20pace.%20And%20he%0Adidn't%20want%20to%20rely%20on%20anyone%20else%20anymore.%20Thus%2C%20the%20project%20was%20born.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EKitten%20curation%20is%20an%20ongoing%20activity.%20It%20takes%20approximately%20one%0Aminute%20(amortized)%20to%20pick%2C%20acquire%2C%20and%20properly%20document%20each%20image.%0ASo%2C%20in%20order%20to%20have%20a%20full%20year's%20worth%20of%20un-repeated%20images%0A(24%20*%20365%20%3D%208%2C760%20images)%2C%20it%20would%20take%20about%20146%20hours.%20That's%20equivalent%0Ato%20a%20full-time%20job%20(of%2040%20hours%20per%20week)%20for%20about%20a%20month.%20Suffice%20it%0Ato%20say%20that%20there%20are%20many%20fewer%20images%20in%20the%20kittenbase%20than%20that%3B%0Ahowever%2C%20we%20aspire%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20curation%20such%20that%20you%20won't%20get%0Atired%20of%20the%20selection%2C%20and%20that%20you%20will%20always%20have%20at%20least%20a%20few%0Anew%20images%20to%20look%20forward%20to%20seeing%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPLEASE%20NOTE%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Kitten%20curation%20has%20been%20on%20hiatus%20since%20around%20the%0Astart%20of%202020%2C%20because%20%5Bgestures%20around%5D.%20We%20hope%20to%20get%20back%20to%20it%20soon%20but%20can%0Amake%20no%20promises.%20But%20FWIW%2C%20here%20is%20the%20official%20submission%20procedure%2C%20should%0Acuration%20ramp%20up%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Ch2%3ESubmissions%3C%2Fh2%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EDo%20you%20have%20(access%20to)%20a%20cute%20kitten%20who%20needs%20more%20exposure%20on%20social%0Amedia%3F%20If%20so%2C%20here%20are%20the%20steps%20to%20follow%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Col%3E%0A%3Cli%3ETake%20pictures%20of%20the%20little%20scamp.%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3Cli%3EUpload%20them%20to%20any%20well-known%20image%20hosting%20site%20which%20provides%20clear%0A%20%20authorship%20attribution%20of%20images.%20For%20example%2C%20Flickr%20is%20a%20good%20choice.%0A%20%20As%20a%20counterexample%2C%20Imgur%20is%20a%20%3Ci%3Ebad%3C%2Fi%3E%20choice%20because%20they%20don't%20provide%0A%20%20solid%20authorship%20attribution.%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3Cli%3EMark%20the%20pictures%20as%20being%20licensed%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license%20that%0A%20%20allows%20sharing%20and%20commercial%20use.%20(Why%20commercial%3F%20Because%20we're%20being%0A%20%20conservative%20in%20what%20we%20accept.%20We%20do%20not%20intend%20to%20%22monetize%22%0A%20%20Hourly%20Kitten.)%20The%0A%20%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Flicenses%2Fby%2F4.0%2F%22%3ECC%20BY%204.0%0A%20%20license%3C%2Fa%3E%20works%2C%20for%20example.%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESend%20mail%20to%20hourlykitten%40murtbo.com%2C%20with%20the%20subject%20line%20%22Submission%2C%22%0A%20%20and%20include%20a%20link%20to%20your%20pictures.%0A%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EHourly%20Kitten%20is%20strictly%20an%20off-hours%20project%2C%20so%20it%20may%20take%20a%20while%20for%0Ayour%20pictures%20to%20get%20included.%20Dan%20looks%20at%20each%20picture%2C%20and%20he%20may%0Anot%20accept%20yours.%20(Sorry.)%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EBeyond%20licensing%2C%20here%20are%20the%20basic%20criteria%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Cul%3E%0A%3Cli%3EThe%20picture%20is%20primarily%20of%20one%20or%20more%20kittens%2C%20yearling%20or%20younger.%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3Cli%3EIt%20is%20an%20unadulterated%2C%20or%20only%20mildly%20manipulated%2C%20photograph.%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3Cli%3EIt's%20an%20aesthetically%20pleasing%20composition.%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3Cli%3EIt's%20cute%20%2F%20twee%20%2F%20squee-worthy.%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3Cli%3EThere%20aren't%20many%20(or%20any)%20non-kitten%20creatures%20in%20the%20picture.%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3Cli%3EThere's%20no%20%22meme%20text.%22%3C%2Fli%3E%0A%3C%2Ful%3E%0A%0A%3Cp%3EThanks%20in%20advance%20for%20your%20submissions!%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%0A%3Ctable%20class%3D%22footer%22%3E%0A%3Ctbody%3E%3Ctr%3E%0A%20%20%3Ctd%3ESite%20copyright%20%C2%A9%201994%E2%80%932024%20Dan%20Bornstein.%20All%20rights%20reserved.%3C%2Ftd%3E%0A%20%20%3Ctd%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22%2F%22%3Emilk.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20%2F%20hourlykitten%3C%2Ftd%3E%0A%3C%2Ftr%3E%0A%3C%2Ftbody%3E%3C%2Ftable%3E%0A%0A%0A%0A%3C%2Fbody%3E%0A%3C%2Fbody%3E%0A%3C%